<br>
Just a theory here, did the monk have his back turned to the mob as well?  So that he wasn't blocking, dodging, and riposting?  All things that could concievably keep him higher on the agro list, not to mention proximity to the mob.  Since he was being hit odds are he had less than max hit points and the warrior had more.  I'm not talking frenzie levels, but perhapse 1 point more agro from taunt won't help enough to counter hit point agro, from a person having lower hit points, unless your attacking.<br>
<br>
All just theories, but things to consider in your test. <p>Lomack, Evoker<br>
